    "recap_headline": "Florida Atlantic University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BOCA RATON, Fla. \u00a0\u2013\nFlorida Atlantic baseball fell to Florida Gulf Coast 12-4 on Tuesday in midweek non-conference action. The Owls begin American Conference play this weekend with an overall record of 13-8.\nTHE BEGINNING\nFGCU (17-4) opened the scoring in the first inning. Three singles followed by a three-run home run gave the Eagles an early 4-0 advantage. The Owls responded with two in the bottom of the first.\nKyle Boylston\nled off with a solo home run.\nBrett Patten\nlater made it 4-2 with an RBI single through the right side.\nTHE TURNING POINT\nThe Eagles hit a pair of two-run homers in the third and fifth innings to lead 9-2. The Owls had a chance to cut into that deficit with the bases loaded and no outs in the bottom of the fifth. But a foul out followed by two strikeouts ended the threat with the deficit still at seven.\nTHE FINISH\nThe visitors added a run in the sixth and two more in the seventh to push the lead to 12-2 before a pair of consolation runs for the Owls made it a 12-4 final.\nTHE BATS\nJohn Martinez\nfinished 3-for-5 with three singles.\nPatten reached base five times with two singles, two walks, and a hit-by-pitch.\nBoylston's home run was his second of the season.\nMichael Perazza\nrecorded his team-leading third triple of the season.\nTHE ARMS\nThe Owls used seven pitchers, highlighted by two perfect innings from\nPatrick Ward\n.\nWard threw 21 pitches and recorded his first collegiate strikeout.\nWHAT'S NEXT\nThe Owls host UTSA this weekend to open the American Conference schedule. First pitch on Friday is set for 6:35 p.m.\nFOLLOW THE OWLS\nTo stay up to date on all things Florida Atlantic baseball, follow us on social media @faubaseball."
  },
